{
  "number": 5264,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5264",
  "title": "Buttons should have a type \"button\" ?",
  "body": "It appears that in the latest version of React InstantSearch (5.3.2) the \"Show More\" button when used in a `<RefinementList />` does not have `type=\"button\"` on the button itself. Some browsers interpret this as a submit button and will attempt to submit a parent `<form>` element if clicked. Can `type=\"button\"` be added so that clicking this only interacts with the `<RefinementList />` options?",
